latestPosts.caption:
**Weddings are beautiful… until it’s time to say goodbye.** 

Being the first daughter to get married in 15 years has been an emotional storm—joy, nostalgia, and tears all woven into one. I thought I was prepared, but nothing could have readied me for the moment my parents looked at me with tearful eyes, still seeing the little girl they once carried in their arms. 

And then there’s my sisters- the one who knows me better than anyone, the one who shared my secrets, my late-night giggles, and my loudest fights.

Leaving home isn’t just about stepping into a new life; it’s about leaving behind a part of your soul with the people who made you who you are. And as I walk away, I know I’m not just taking memories—I’m leaving pieces of my heart behind.

latestPosts.caption:
Bride-to-be’s take notes!

Discover the best of wedding shop in Delhi at these 5 markets!

Chandni Chowk – Delhi’s bridal haven — where @asianacoutureofficial timeless charm, @sudhirbhaisareewala regal silhouettes, and @marwarcouture intricate craftsmanship come together to create every bride’s perfect ensembleFrom budget-friendly finds to grand designer-inspired pieces, it caters to all!

Mehrauli –Home to the best of the designers like @manishmalhotraworld @sabyasachiofficial, @dollyjstudio @gazalguptacouture @perniaspopupshop and @falgunishanepeacockindia , @sulakshanamonga @rahulmishra_7
Mehrauli is pure luxury. Be warned—you might end up spending more than planned, but it’ll be worth it!

Shahpur Jat – South Delhi’s best-kept secret for timeless bridal fashion! Discover elegant lehengas, gowns, and suits from labels like @bageechabanaras , @devnagri_offcial @kalista.official , @lizpaulofficial — perfect for the modern bride with a taste for sophistication

Dhan Mill – For brides looking for contemporary elegance, Dhan Mill is a must-visit! this place is all about mirrorwork, pastels, and fusion,
silhouettes. With designers like @abhinavmishra_ , @mahimamahajanofficial and @swishbydolcyandsimran @seemagujraldesign , @jjvalaya , @nappadori @qbikofficial you’ll find a unique blend of modern and traditional aesthetics.

South Extension – The ultmate destination for your luxury shopping.  Discover timeless lehengas, sarees, and suits from premium labels like @ejaazcouture , @frontierraas, @rimpleandharpreet , @azafashions  and @meenabazaar — perfect for every bride-to-be who loves classic elegance with a modern touch”

We made the impossible possible- to share our first look together before the wedding 

So I always wanted him to have the first look before our wedding, and yes I had made that very clear to him…
But you know Indian weddings, apparently got stuck with the rituals and then he wasn’t allowed to go back from the baraat
There I was panicking and upset because having him get the first look was super important to me
I had my family members knocking on the door to see me, but I said NO

Stay tuned to see the first look moments in part-2!
